<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-151-390 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 957 856</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  May 20 1991 v8 n10 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell creates support alliance: key third parties unite toredefine service, troubleshooting methods. (Technical SupportAlliance)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Breidenbach, Susan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Novell announces the formation of the Technical Support Alliance(TSA), a consortium of hardware and software vendors intended tosimplify the process of obtaining service for a multivendorNetware local area network (LAN) while eliminating the uselessrecriminations that often accompany such service requests.andP;  Underthe terms of the agreement, Novell and 11 other vendors willestablish official channels of communication and provide forcross-training of support staff.andP;  Charter members of the TSAinclude Apple, Compaq, HP, IBM, Borland, 3Com, Intel, Microsoft,Netframe, Oracle, and Ungermann-Bass.andP;  The TSA stands apart fromexisting multivendor mutual support agreements in terms of thelevel of commitment and resources being supplied by each member,and in the infrastructure that will coordinate the services.andO;Novell, at the center of the agreement, will have an initial totalof 22 individuals dedicated to the TSA, a primary and secondarycontact person for each of the other vendors.andP;  Users will be ableto dial a single, 800 number to obtain answers to all questionsregarding their multivendor LAN.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (Services).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Product:   NetWare (Network operating system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     ConsortiaSupport ServicesMultivendor SystemsVendor Relations.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   TSA membership. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>